command:example.dev:code: AdvancedSearch with multiple criteria/filters

dev:remarks.maml:para: Search with datascan for all IP matching the criteria : Apache web server listening on 443 tcp port hosted on Windows C:\PS> Search-OnypheInfo -AdvancedSearch @("product:Apache","port:443","os:Windows") -SearchType datascan

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- EXAMPLE 2 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: simple search with one filter/criteria

dev:remarks.maml:para: Search with threatlist for all IP matching the criteria : all IP from russia tagged by threat lists C:\PS> Search-OnypheInfo -SimpleSearchValue RU -SearchType threatlist -SimpleSearchFilter country

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- EXAMPLE 3 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: AdvancedSearch with multiple criteria/filters and set the API key

dev:remarks.maml:para: Search with datascan for all IP matching the criteria : Apache web server listening on 443 tcp port hosted on Windows C:\PS> Search-OnypheInfo -AdvancedSearch @("product:Apache","port:443","os:Windows") -SearchType datascan -apikey "xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- EXAMPLE 4 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: simple search with one filter/criteria and request page 2 of the results

dev:remarks.maml:para: Search with threatlist for all IP matching the criteria : all IP from russia tagged by threat lists C:\PS> Search-OnypheInfo -SimpleSearchValue RU -SearchType threatlist -SimpleSearchFilter country -page "2"

maml:Description.maml:para: -Proxy{Proxy} Set the proxy URL
-ProxyCredential{ProxyCredential} Set the proxy credential to be authenticated with the internet proxy set
-DirectNoProxy Remove proxy and configure Onyphe powershell functions to use a direct connection
-ProxyUseDefaultCredentials Use current security context to be authenticated with the internet proxy set
-AnonymousProxy No authentication (open proxy) with the internet proxy set
